President Obama expresses his horror and sadness at the terrorist attack at Garissa University College in Kenya. He condemns the brutal massacre of innocent men and women, many of whom were students pursuing a better life. The President also commends the responders who lost their lives in protecting the students and faculty. He acknowledges the resilience and decency of the Kenyan people and vows to stand with them against terrorism. President Obama believes that the future of Kenya will be shaped by young people like those at Garissa University College, and he plans to deliver this message during his visit to Kenya in July. The President assures the Kenyan people that the United States is their unwavering friend and ally.